cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.MA, cs.SY, cs.DS 

This paper focuses on developing a networking mechanism for mobile devices to overcome processing power and energy bottlenecks, which are becoming primary concerns in device-to-device networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of cellular and Wi-Fi links, which falls under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The use of cooperative mobile devices and evaluation on a testbed can be categorized under cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also proposes a framework for energy-aware computation, which can be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
